<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Pinus</i> <i>torreyana</i> is dominant in the tree canopy or is emergent over a shrub canopy with <i>Adenostoma</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>confertiflora</i>, <i>Artemisia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Baccharis</i> <i>pilularis</i>, <i>Ceanothus</i> <i>arboreus</i>, <i>Ceanothus</i> <i>verrucosus</i>, <i>Cneoridium</i> <i>dumosum</i>, <i>Coreopsis</i> <i>gigantea</i>, <i>Coreopsis</i> <i>maritima</i>, <i>Diplacus</i> <i>parviflorus</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Eriophyllum</i> <i>confertiflorum</i>, <i>Heteromeles</i> <i>arbutifolia</i>, <i>Lotus</i> <i>dendroideus</i>, <i>Quercus</i> <i>berberidifolia</i>, <i>Quercus</i> <i>pacifica</i>, <i>Rhus</i> <i>integrifolia</i> and <i>Salvia</i> spp. The herbaceous layer commonly includes <i>Achillea</i> <i>millefolium</i>, <i>Bromus</i> <i>diandrus</i>, <i>Carex</i> <i>globosa</i>, <i>Corethrogyne</i> <i>filaginifolia</i>, <i>Pentagramma</i> <i>triangularis</i> or <i>Pseudognaphalium</i> <i>biolettii</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text"> Trees < 15 m; canopy is intermittent or open. Shrub layer is sparse to intermittent. Herbaceous layer is sparse or abundant. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Pinus torreyana</i> is the sole dominant in the tree canopy (Evens and San 2005, Sproul et al. 2011, Rodriguez et al. 2017).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Coastal bluffs, maritime terraces, slopes. Soils are sandstone or diatomaceous derived.  </div>
</div>

        
