<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Infrequent, severe fires are important for seedling establishment although disturbance is not essential (McMaster 1980). <i>Pinus torreyana </i>has a delayed seed response, probably in response to varying and infrequent fire cycles. It is fire-intolerant. Low-severity fires will kill small trees
even if no crown damage is sustained (Zedler et al. 1987), and severe fires kills trees of all sizes (McMaster 1980). Seed drop from cones is substantial immediately after crown fire; some seeds gradually release from cones for over 10 years after a fire (McMaster 1980, 1982, McMaster and Zedler 1981). According to Zedler et al. (1987), maintaining a natural system may require that it be allowed to burn to the ground every century.</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
